Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) has approved the constitution of an Interim Management Team headed by Mr. Mutiu Olaniyi Adio Sunmonu. The interim management team is expected  to oversee the affairs of Oando Plc, and conduct an Extra Ordinary General Meeting on or before July 1, 2019 to appoint new directors to the board of the company. The new directors, according to SEC, will subsequently select a management team for Oando Plc. “The Commission wishes to reiterate its commitment to maintaining the integrity of the market” , SEC said in the statement.